FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - CHINA
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed/html>
See Also
Foot & mouth disease, import ban - China 990228100922,
990327225526
Foot & mouth disease - China (Yunnan) 981009171020
Date: Fri, 04 Jun 1999 09:52:45 +0200
From: EMPRES-Livestock <EMPRES-Livestock@fao.org

The following communication to FAO has been received from Mr Jia Youling,
the Director-General of the Bureau of Animal Production and Health,
Beijing, China.
Reports received on May 20, 1999 from Fujian, Hainan and Tibet, there are
outbreaks of Foot and Mouth Disease (FMD):
Location: Ningde City, Fujian Provinde
Number of Outbreaks: 2
Species: Swine
Suceptible: 58
Cases: 12
Destroyed: 70
Location: Baisha County Hainan Province
Number of outbreaks: 1
Species: Bovine
Susceptible: ---
Cases: 8
Destroyed: 8
Location: Rikeze, Tibet
Number of outbreaks: 5
Species: Bovine Swine
Susceptible: --- ----
Cases: 60 1195
Destroyed 60 1195
Diagnosis:
A. Nature of diagnosis: clinicl and laboratory
B. Causal agent: FMD virus type O
Epidemiology: Source of agent/origin of infection: tracing back under way
Control measures taken during reporting period:
A. Destroy the infected and susceptible animals.
B. Ban on the movement of animals to other districts.
C. Emergency vaccination.
This follows a report from last year which described outbreaks of FMD virus
type O in two bordering counties (Dima and Menglian) in Yunnan Province in
July 1998.
